#Implements installing of Chocolatey packages from the web using choco:// Protocol and chocoProtocolStub.exe

###WHO IS THIS FOR?
**chocoprotocolstub** is designed for those who aren't comfortable with the Command Prompt or just don't like to type much. **chocoprotocolstub** allows you to install Chocolatey packages by simply clicking choco:// URLs in your web browser. **chocoprotocolstub** is also useful to support professionals who know the difficulty of getting end users to type in commands correctly, now you can give them a URL to click and have a Chocolatey package installed!

If you like the convienance of this package, you should also check out [Install Chocolatey Packages from your Web Browser](https://chocolatey.org/packages/choco-install-packages-from-web-winconfig) which is very similar in concept and [(unofficial) Chocolatey Shortcuts (Config)](https://chocolatey.org/packages/choco-shortcuts-winconfig).

###HOW DOES IT WORK?
**chocoprotocolstub** configures Windows to use choco://packagename URLs and pass them along to **chocoProtocolStub.exe** which then processes the URL and runs Chocolatey's cinst.exe ("choco install" shim) to install the package. [Lets hope this functionality gets built into a future version of Chocolatey](https://github.com/chocolatey/choco/issues/1680) and then this package can be deprecated. **chocoprotocolstub** also sets cinst.exe to always run as administrator which is necessary for most packages.

###USAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
Just click a choco://packagename URL on a web page and the package will install after one or two approval clicks. 
Browser examples: [Chrome](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bcurran3/ChocolateyPackages/master/chocoprotocolstub\chocoprotocolstub_chrome_example.png) | [Firefox](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bcurran3/ChocolateyPackages/master/chocoprotocolstub\chocoprotocolstub_firefox_example.png) | [Opera](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bcurran3/ChocolateyPackages/master/chocoprotocolstub\chocoprotocolstub_opera_example.png)

**Easy peasy, Chocolateasy!**

